


                            Server creation - Express 


                1. create server folder

                2. install package.json - npm init

                3. create index.js

                4. install express - npm i express

                5. Import express in index.js 

                6. create app using express

                7. set port

                8. Run server- node index.js

                9. define router : - expressApp.HTTPmethod(path,call back function)

                10. RUN SERVER - nodemon index.js

                11. install & import session: npm i express-session

                12. Middlewares - 

                    12.1 Application specific Middlewares

                    12.2 router Level Middlewares

                13. JSON Web Token (JWT) - npm i jsonwebtoken

                    13.1 Token Generation

                    13.2 Token Validation

                14. MongoDB Connection: 

                    14.1 install mongoose : syntax: npm i mongoose

                    14.2 Import mongoose

                    14.2 Using connection string to connect mongoDb with server

                    14.3 Model created  

                15. Solving Asynchronous events - promise 

                    15.1 then used to defined resolved state 

                16. Cors - Cross origin resourse sharing { npm i cors }